    "engine": "knitr",
    "markdown": "---\nproject:\n  type: website\n\nwebsite:\n  title: \"How Video Game Music Expanded from 8-bit Loops to Cinematic Scores\"\n  navbar:\n    left:\n      - href: index.qmd\n        text: Home\n      - href: data.qmd\n        text: Data\n      - href: findings.qmd\n        text: Findings\n      - href: reflection.qmd\n        text: Reflection\n\nformat:\n  html:\n    theme: cosmo\n    toc: true\n    page-layout: full\n---\n\n## Introduction\n\nVideo game music has evolved dramatically over the past four decades. Early games relied on short looping melodies due to hardware limitations, while modern games feature expansive cinematic scores.\n\nThis project investigates how video game soundtrack **size and structure** have changed across technological eras.\n\n---\n\n## Dataset\n\nThe dataset was manually constructed from video game soundtrack tracklists.\n\nEach row represents a **single track** and includes:\n\n- Game\n- Release year\n- Technological era\n- Track title\n- Track duration\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(timechange)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'timechange' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(lubridate)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'lubridate' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n\nAttaching package: 'lubridate'\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nThe following objects are masked from 'package:base':\n\n    date, intersect, setdiff, union\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(tidyverse)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'tidyverse' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'tibble' was built under R version 4.5.2\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'tidyr' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'readr' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'purrr' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'dplyr' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'stringr' was built under R version 4.5.2\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'forcats' was built under R version 4.5.2\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n── Attaching core tidyverse packages ──────────────────────── tidyverse 2.0.0 ──\n✔ dplyr   1.2.0     ✔ readr   2.2.0\n✔ forcats 1.0.1     ✔ stringr 1.6.0\n✔ ggplot2 4.0.2     ✔ tibble  3.3.1\n✔ purrr   1.2.1     ✔ tidyr   1.3.2\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n── Conflicts ────────────────────────────────────────── tidyverse_conflicts() ──\n✖ dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()\n✖ dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()\nℹ Use the conflicted package (<http://conflicted.r-lib.org/>) to force all conflicts to become errors\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nlibrary(plotly)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\nWarning: package 'plotly' was built under R version 4.4.3\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n\nAttaching package: 'plotly'\n\nThe following object is masked from 'package:ggplot2':\n\n    last_plot\n\nThe following object is masked from 'package:stats':\n\n    filter\n\nThe following object is masked from 'package:graphics':\n\n    layout\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ndf <- read.csv(\"video_game_ost_cleaned_with_seconds.csv\")\n\nhead(df)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  game year    era Track.Number                    Track.Title Track.Length\n1 Halo 2001 CD_Era            1                  Opening Suite     03:33:00\n2 Halo 2001 CD_Era            2 Truth and Reconciliation Suite     08:25:00\n3 Halo 2001 CD_Era            3               Brothers in Arms     01:29:00\n4 Halo 2001 CD_Era            4             Enough Dead Heroes     03:00:00\n5 Halo 2001 CD_Era            5               Perilous Journey     02:26:00\n6 Halo 2001 CD_Era            6            A Walk in the Woods     01:52:00\n  Duration_sec\n1        12780\n2        30300\n3         5340\n4        10800\n5         8760\n6         6720\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n# Games Included \n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nunique(df$game)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n [1] \"Halo\"                                \n [2] \"Metal Gear Solid\"                    \n [3] \"Super Mario 64\"                      \n [4] \"The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time\"\n [5] \"Mega Man\"                            \n [6] \"Sonic The Hedgehog\"                  \n [7] \"Super Mario Bros\"                    \n [8] \"The Legend of Zelda\"                 \n [9] \"Minecraft\"                           \n[10] \"Skyrim\"                              \n[11] \"The Last of Us\"                      \n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n# Creating Game-Level Summary Statistics \n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ngame_summary <- df |>\n  group_by(game, year, era) |>\n  summarise(\n    total_tracks = n(),\n    total_runtime_sec = sum(Duration_sec)\n  ) |>\n  mutate(total_runtime_min = total_runtime_sec / 60)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n`summarise()` has regrouped the output.\nℹ Summaries were computed grouped by game, year, and era.\nℹ Output is grouped by game and year.\nℹ Use `summarise(.groups = \"drop_last\")` to silence this message.\nℹ Use `summarise(.by = c(game, year, era))` for per-operation grouping\n  (`?dplyr::dplyr_by`) instead.\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n# Growth of Soundtrack Size \n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\np <- ggplot(game_summary, aes(x = year, y = total_runtime_min, text = game)) +\n  geom_point(size = 3) +\n  geom_smooth(method = \"lm\", se = FALSE) +\n  theme_minimal()\n\nggplotly(p, tooltip = c(\"x\", \"y\", \"text\"))\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n`geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-cf5c224e6c74889d7d3f\" style=\"width:100%;height:464px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-cf5c224e6c74889d7d3f\">{\"x\":{\"data\":[{\"x\":[2001,2002,1987,1991,1998,2011,2011,1991,1997,1986,2013,1986,1998],\"y\":[1938,740,2121,263,3246,3530,3510,776,2025,1845,1985,1118,2688],\"text\":[\"year: 2001<br />total_runtime_min: 1938<br />Halo\",\"year: 2002<br />total_runtime_min:  740<br />Halo\",\"year: 1987<br />total_runtime_min: 2121<br />Mega Man\",\"year: 1991<br />total_runtime_min:  263<br />Mega Man\",\"year: 1998<br />total_runtime_min: 3246<br />Metal Gear Solid\",\"year: 2011<br />total_runtime_min: 3530<br />Minecraft\",\"year: 2011<br />total_runtime_min: 3510<br />Skyrim\",\"year: 1991<br />total_runtime_min:  776<br />Sonic The Hedgehog\",\"year: 1997<br />total_runtime_min: 2025<br />Super Mario 64\",\"year: 1986<br />total_runtime_min: 1845<br />Super Mario Bros\",\"year: 2013<br />total_runtime_min: 1985<br />The Last of Us\",\"year: 1986<br />total_runtime_min: 1118<br />The Legend of Zelda\",\"year: 1998<br />total_runtime_min: 2688<br />The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time\"],\"type\":\"scatter\",\"mode\":\"markers\",\"marker\":{\"autocolorscale\":false,\"color\":\"rgba(0,0,0,1)\",\"opacity\":1,\"size\":11.338582677165356,\"symbol\":\"circle\",\"line\":{\"width\":1.8897637795275593,\"color\":\"rgba(0,0,0,1)\"}},\"hoveron\":\"points\",\"showlegend\":false,\"xaxis\":\"x\",\"yaxis\":